WEBVTT

00:03.150 --> 00:07.501
Hello everyone welcome to nexteditor.dev Today I would

00:07.501 --> 00:12.163
like to show you a project that I implemented like a social

00:12.163 --> 00:17.040
newsfeed application with infinite scrolling.

00:17.040 --> 00:20.675
Before looking at the implementation, let me quickly walk

00:20.675 --> 00:24.310
through the package dot JSON file and introduce the tech

00:24.310 --> 00:27.940
stack used in this project.

00:29.230 --> 00:33.946
This project is built with React and TypeScript. We use

00:33.946 --> 00:38.745
Vite for development and built performance for data fetching and

00:38.745 --> 00:43.600
state management, we use TanStack React Query.

00:43.600 --> 00:48.903
For infinite scrolling and optimized list rendering we use

00:48.903 --> 00:54.115
TanStack React Virtual and axios is for API communication.

00:54.115 --> 00:58.490
Now the project is already rendering.

00:58.490 --> 01:06.050
So uh, I will minimize the console and expand the preview.

01:06.050 --> 01:12.230
So you can open the preview UI from this button.

01:12.680 --> 01:17.691
So we can focus on the application UI. As you can see, this

01:17.691 --> 01:22.703
is social newsfeed interface with infinite scrolling. Now

01:22.703 --> 01:26.730
let's move to the implementation.

01:26.730 --> 01:32.750
First, let's open App.tsx file.

01:32.750 --> 01:38.150
App.tsx is the main entry point of the application.

01:38.150 --> 01:43.520
Here we call the useTrendingStatuses custom hook to fetch

01:43.520 --> 01:48.440
trending statuses and manage timeline data.

01:48.440 --> 01:54.087
Then we pass the return data into TrendingStatusList

01:54.087 --> 01:59.255
to display the newsfeed. Next, let's open the use

01:59.255 --> 02:03.170
trending statuses hook.

02:04.500 --> 02:09.980
OK this custom hook handle data fetching and pagination?

02:09.980 --> 02:16.240
Here we use use infinite query from TanStack React Query.

02:16.240 --> 02:21.980
To load data page by page and support infinite scrolling.

02:21.980 --> 02:25.810
We also manage loading and error.

02:25.810 --> 02:28.580
And pagination states.

02:28.580 --> 02:33.410
Now let's open the trending status list component. This

02:33.410 --> 02:38.740
component is responsible for rendering the newsfeed.

02:38.740 --> 02:43.526
To improve performance we use tanstack react virtual so only

02:43.526 --> 02:48.180
visible items are rendered on the screen.

02:48.180 --> 02:54.540
When user's scrolling, more data is loaded automatically.

02:54.540 --> 03:01.010
And for this card design we separate the component

03:01.010 --> 03:07.430
Post Card, so let's see the PostCard component.

03:07.430 --> 03:11.925
This uh this component is responsible for rendering each

03:11.925 --> 03:16.657
individual post design like this. Separating components and

03:16.657 --> 03:22.680
hook helps keep the project clean and maintainable.

03:23.340 --> 03:28.107
OK, that's a brief overview of the implementation in our

03:28.107 --> 03:30.800
NextEditor.dev.

03:30.800 --> 03:34.160
Thank you for watching.
